# Import CSV Data to MongoDB Atlas

We need to import the data from `customer_support_tickets_200k.csv` (located in the root directory) into MongoDB Atlas. The backend app connects to Atlas if the `MONGODB_URI` environment variable is defined. We will create a robust standalone import script in the backend directory that parses the CSV file, maps the CSV schema to the Mongoose Ticket schema, batches the inserts for high performance, and allows configuration of the import limit and clearing of the database.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Data Size & MongoDB Atlas Free Tier Limitations**
> The CSV file contains **200,000 tickets** (~73.8 MB). 
> - A free-tier MongoDB Atlas cluster (M0) typically has a storage limit of **512 MB**.
> - Importing all 200,000 tickets (including indexing and metadata) might get close to or exceed the storage quota and could impact performance.
> - Therefore, our import script will include a **default limit of 1,000 tickets** to prevent exceeding Atlas's quotas, but will support command-line arguments to import more or the entire dataset if you wish.

> [!WARNING]
> **Gemini API Embeddings During Import**
> - Generating text embeddings via Gemini API for all 200,000 tickets is not feasible due to API rate limits and quota.
> - The import script will set the `embedding` array field to empty `[]`.
> - The application is designed to generate and cache embeddings on the fly if they are missing (e.g. when an agent views a ticket and requests suggestions), so the core application logic remains fully functional.

## Open Questions

There are no blocking open questions. We will use the following default field mappings:
- **Title**: Constructed as `${category} Ticket #${ticket_id} (${product})`.
- **Category**: Mapped from the CSV's 10 categories to the Mongoose Schema's 3 enums (`Billing`, `Technical`, `Feature Request`).
- **Priority**: Mapped from `Urgent` -> `High`, `High`/`Medium`/`Low` -> corresponding schema values.
- **Status**: Mapped from `Closed`/`Resolved` -> `Resolved`, `In Progress`/`Pending Customer` -> `In Progress`, `Open` -> `Open`.
- **Messages**: 
  - A customer message containing the `issue_description` is added.
  - If the ticket is resolved, an agent message containing the `resolution_notes` is added.
- **Summary**: A short summary will be auto-generated during import containing the customer's name, email, product, and channel.

