## Proposed Changes

### Backend Database Import Script

We will create a standalone script to run the import.

#### [NEW] [import-csv.js](file:///d:/vs%20codes/project%201/backend/import-csv.js)
A utility script that will:
1. Load credentials from `backend/.env`.
2. Connect to MongoDB Atlas.
3. Stream the CSV file from the root directory using `csv-parser` to save memory.
4. Process rows in batches (default size 500) and map them to Mongoose Schema requirements.
5. Insert documents using Mongoose `insertMany`.
6. Support arguments like `--limit <number>` (default: 1000) and `--clear` (to clear the collection before importing).

